Citation.sAbstract: Heat capacity for 1-butyl-3-methylimidazolium nitrate [C4mim][NO3] in the temperature range (5 to 370) K has been measured by adiabatic calorimetry. Temperatures and enthalpies of its phase transitions have been determined. Thermodynamic functions have been calculated for crystalline and liquid states. Hygroscopicity of [C4mim][NO3] has been measured. Phase transition temperatures for set of nitrate salts have been compared. Enthalpy of combustion and enthalpy of formation for crystalline [C4mim][NO3] have been determined using a static-bomb isoperibol combustion calorimeter. A correlation scheme for estimation of Cp of ionic liquids has been developed.
